decision_conditions:
The Head of Highways Services (Engineering), PO Box 3333, 222 Upper Street, London N1 1YA (tel. 020 7527 2000) must be consulted for:
(i)	the need to comply with the Highways act 1980 for any alterations needed to existing pavement or kerb to drive a vehicle onto private property or land;
(ii)	the need to comply with the Islington (Parking Places) Traffic Management Order, as amended for the suspension or temporary/permanent revocation of any on-street parking places;
(iii)	the need to comply with the Highways Act 1980 for maintenance, repair or reinstatement works on or under the public highway;
(iv)	the need to complete and submit the 'standard form' to the Assistant Head of Environment and Leisure Services (Engineering) with appropriate plans, levels and programme dates.
